Some spare parts stores around the Alapeju section of the Ladipo Market, Mushin, Lagos State, have been gutted by fire on Sunday. As of the time of filing this report, no casualty had been recorded. Confirming the incident via its Twitter handle, @lagosrescue, the Lagos State Fire and Rescue Services said, “We are currently attending to Fire emergency at spare parts sales line, Alapeju section of Ladipo Market, Mushin-Lagos, after quelling a residential fire at 36, Abeokuta Expressway, Cement, Dopemu, Lagos.” Details later…